Conditional Statements
=========================

1.If CONDITION if(condition) {}
--------------
The Statements gets executed only when the given condition is true.
If the condition is false then the statements inside if statement body are completely ignored.

2.If else CONDITION if(condition) {} else {}
-------------------
The Statements inside "if" would execute if the condition is true, 
and the statements inside "else" would execute if the condition is false.

3.if-else-if CONDITION
---------------------- 
if-else-if statement is used when we need to check multiple conditions.
In this statement we have only one "if" and one "else",
however we can have multiple "else if".
It is also known as if else if ladder.

4.Switch Case CONDITION
-----------------------
Switch case statement is used when we have number of options (or choices)
and we may need to perform a different task for each choice.